Why is a circular buffer more cache-friendly than a linked-list queue?

A circular buffer is more cache-friendly because its elements are stored next to each other in memory, while a linked list stores elements at random memory locations.

Circular Buffer
[10][20][30][40][50]

When the CPU loads 10, it often loads 20, 30, 40, etc. into cache at the same time.

✅ Fewer cache misses
✅ Faster memory access

Linked List
10 -> 20 -> 30 -> 40

The nodes might be stored like:

10 @ address 1000
20 @ address 50000
30 @ address 2000
40 @ address 90000

The CPU must jump around memory to find the next node.

❌ More cache misses
❌ Slower memory access
